30/01/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Alvaro de Soto, the UN's Special Envoy to Cyprus, met Turkish ruling party leader Recep Tayyip Erdogan on Wednesday (29 January) to discuss possible Turkish mediation in negotiations between the Greek and Turkish communities in Cyprus.
De Soto officially sought Turkish assistance in persuading Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktash to sit at the bargaining table.
Erdogan said Turkey would continue to support the peace process on the island and do what it can to find a solution both sides consider reasonable.
(Milliyet - 30/01/03;
Anadolu Agency, AFP - 29/01/03)
